    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A single-page, narrative scrolling application designed to guide school leadership through the event proposal. The structure mirrors a persuasive pitch: introducing the concept, highlighting student benefits, showcasing a filterable gallery of potential games with video links, detailing the practical logistics with an updated budget chart, and ending with a clear 'ask'. This enhanced structure provides more choice and clarity for decision-makers. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: Student Benefits -> Viz: Interactive icon cards -> Interaction: Click to reveal description -> Justification: Engaging exploration of benefits.
        - Report Info: Sample Games (Expanded List) -> Goal: Inform, Excite, & Offer Choice -> Viz: A filterable grid of game cards (HTML/CSS/JS) -> Interaction: Filter by category, click card to open a webpage with instructions -> Justification: Provides a wide, organized selection of games for leadership to consider, with text-based instructions for easy review.
        - Report Info: Budget ($30) -> Goal: Inform & Justify -> Viz: Donut Chart (Chart.js/Canvas) -> Interaction: Hover for tooltips -> Justification: Visually represents the new, lower budget, emphasizing the event's high value and low cost.
        - CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
